Self-compassion & SDO Study

Polina Beloborodova

10/5/2020

Sample

The data were collected from 578 students of the University of Hawaiʻi at Mānoa in the Spring (N = 91) and Fall (N = 487) semesters of 2019. Mean age was 20.11 years (SD = 3.82). Participants self-identified as female (67.99%), male (31.49%), and other gender (3 persons). Self-reported ethnicity was distributed as follows: Asian (42.56%), White (non-Hispanic, 22.15%), Multicultural (18.17%), Hawaiian/Pacific Islander (6.92%), Hispanic (5.54%), Other (2.08%), Black (non-Hispanic, 1.73%), and Native American (5 persons).
